Project Context: I am building a 12-page Streamlit macro finance dashboard. Every new Python script, chart, or UI element you write must strictly follow my "Bloomberg Terminal" aesthetic.

Core Styling Rules:

Backgrounds: Pure Black (#000000) or Dark Grey (#0a0a0a for cards/sidebars).

Typography: Monospace only ('Courier New', Courier, monospace).

Data & Body Text: Neon Green (#00FF00), size 14px.

Headers & Accents: Bloomberg Amber (#FFB100), uppercase, with dark borders (#333333).

Charts (Plotly): Always use template='plotly_dark', paper_bgcolor="rgba(0,0,0,0)", and hardcode the line colors to high-contrast neon hex codes.

Execution: Always include the custom HTML/CSS injection block via st.markdown(unsafe_allow_html=True) at the top of any new page to override default Streamlit styling.